The paper deals with pattern matching in strings, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of the Burrows-Wheeler transform is a common technique in string algorithms, and is often used in the context of data compression and indexing. The paper also introduces the concept of degenerate strings, which are a generalization of regular strings, and presents a new method for pattern matching in degenerate strings. This makes the paper relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG).
